All Implemented Interfaces:
Destructible, javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
public class EnemyPlaneOne extends Actor
Represents an enemy plane actor in the game.

EnemyPlaneOne is a specific type of Actor that has a projectile shooting capability, an animation component for explosions, and a defined movement pattern. It interacts with other game components such as the level, sound system, and collision detection.

  • Method Details

    • updateActor

      public void updateActor(double deltaTime, LevelParent level)
      Updates the state of the enemy plane during the game loop.

      This method updates the position of the enemy plane, its hitbox position, and its shooting component. It also ensures that the projectile pool is set for the shooting component.

      Specified by:
      updateActor in class Actor
      Parameters:
      deltaTime - the time elapsed since the last update, in seconds.
      level - the current level of the game.

    • destroy

      public void destroy()
      Destroys the enemy plane, triggering visual and auditory effects.

      This method plays an explosion animation and sound effect. It ensures that the destruction process occurs only once, even if the method is called multiple times.

      Specified by:
      destroy in interface Destructible
      Overrides:
      destroy in class Actor
